http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Taxi-driver-held-for-stealing-money/article13983225.ece

The Nedumbassery police on Tuesday nabbed a taxi driver for a botched attempt to steal 1,400 dollars from the baggage of an Australian couple, who had hired his taxi.Officials said the person, identified as Anoop, 28, a native of Muvattupuzha, was arrested after he picked up an altercation with the middle-aged couple after reaching the Nedumbassery airport.After intervention by the police officers, both the complainants and the accused were taken to the police station nearby.During police interrogation, Anoop confessed to stealing the money and concealing it inside his clothes.